<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>SQL on Code it Yourself...</title><link>https://carlos.mendible.com/tags/sql/</link><description>Recent content in SQL on Code it Yourself...</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><copyright>Copyright &amp;copy; 2020 - Carlos Mendible</copyright><lastBuildDate>Fri, 01 Oct 2010 11:05:49 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://carlos.mendible.com/tags/sql/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>SQL Azure Requires Clustered Indexes in all tables</title><link>https://carlos.mendible.com/2010/10/01/sql-azure-requires-clustered-indexes-in-all-tables/</link><pubDate>Fri, 01 Oct 2010 11:05:49 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://carlos.mendible.com/2010/10/01/sql-azure-requires-clustered-indexes-in-all-tables/</guid><description>&lt;p>Recently we performed some test against SQL Azure. We found that our system was throwing an exception cause SQL Azure requires a clustered index in each table (&lt;a href="http://blogs.msdn.com/b/sqlazure/archive/2010/05/12/10011257.aspx">Wanna know why?&lt;/a>).&lt;/p>
&lt;p>So how can you find out what tables are causing the issue? The answer is simple, run the following query and you&amp;rsquo;ll have the list of tables to fix:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4">&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql">&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">SELECT&lt;/span> name
&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">FROM&lt;/span> sys.objects
&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">WHERE&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">type&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#39;U&amp;#39;&lt;/span>
&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">AND&lt;/span> object_id &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">NOT&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">IN&lt;/span>
(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">SELECT&lt;/span> object_id &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">FROM&lt;/span> sys.indexes &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">WHERE&lt;/span> index_id &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff">1&lt;/span>)
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>Hope it helps!&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>